children.subject: I haven't taken both, but I believe it's beneficial to take 161 AFTER 61C to save yourself some struggling time since you will take 61C anyways

Id recommend 160. There are a few things in 161 you might find a little weird if you haven't taken 61C, but its not like its something you can't get up to speed on in given you'll be taking 61C at the same time. However, with 160, you'll come in with all the "requisite" knowledge.

The beginning of 161 touches on assembly knowledge that you learn from 61C. It's pretty difficult to get through the first project without that background, especially if you've never seen it before. The middle of 161 goes over cryptography, which is covered in 70.

Taking both CS 161 and 16C in the fall.

I am currently taking CS70 this summer and plan to take 61C in the fall. I saw that the pre reqs to 161 include 61C. For those of you who have taken CS 161, is it doable to take 61C while taking 161 or would I need to have finished the entire class before I am able to apply the info learned in 61C to 161?

history.content:
I am currently considering to take CS161(I meet the Math55 prerequisite) together with CS70 and CS61C during Fall, since I've read the HKN workload descriptions and it seems to me that 160 has a lot more workload than 161. But I've heard from several people that 160 is a better option to take with 70 and 61C; Any advice on which one will be less stressful? and why? [I am interested in both classes so subject wise I don't have a preference, but I'd love to pick the less stressful schedule if possible].  

Thanks you!
